This method prioritizes finding a local clock first to avoid unnecessary lookups. If the clock isn't found locally, it attempts a recursive search up the unit hierarchy.

```python
def _getAssociatedClk(self):
        """
        If interface has associated clk return it otherwise
        try to find clk on parent recursively
        """
        a = self._associatedClk

        if a is not None:
            return a

        p = self._parent
        assert p is not None

        if isinstance(p, UnitBase):
            return getClk(p)
        else:
            return p._getAssociatedClk()
```

The function handles clock retrieval by first checking a local association and then delegating the search to its parent until one is found.
